Diagnosis.
Body elongate, parallel, slightly convex and greenish-bronze (
Fig. 1 b
); integument densely and deeply punctate, shagrened; surface among punctures with micropunctures visible at high magnification. Pronotum subrectangular or subtrapezoidal shaped (
Fig. 4
). Four reduced elytral spots. Internal sac of median lobe of aedeagus (
Fig. 5
) with tangled membranes, the dorsal twisted one closer to the apex (lateral view), this slightly bent to the left (dorsal view) (
Fig. 5
).
